Description: Floor fragment of Corinthian black-figured pottery plate with slight remains of moulding or foot on underside; underside: parts of two bands; interior: traces of single black band and some incision lines from undetermined black figure decoration, single incised blob rosette as filling ornament.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.118) (Phase 1)
